description: Approval of Reserved Matters for Block B (comprising Block B1 and B2 of 15 storeys and 22 storeys respectively) to provide a total of 169 residential units (comprising 83 one-bedroom units, 82 two-bedroom units and 4 three-bedroom units) and 571sqm (GEA) of retail/restaurant/cafe floorspace (Use Class A1 and/or A3)), associated hard and soft landscaping and related works pursuant to condition 2, relating to siting, design, external appearance and landscaping for the comprehensive mixed use redevelopment of the outline approval DC/06/62375, dated 08 May 2009 for the Lewisham Gateway Site, SE13 (land between Rennell Street and Lewisham Railway Station) for 100,000m comprising retail (A1, A2, A3, A4 and A5), offices (B1), hotel (C1), residential (C3), education/health (D1) and leisure (D2) with parking and associated infrastructure, as well as open space and water features with up to 57,000 m residential (C3), up to 12,000 m shops, financial & professional services (A1 & A2), up to 17,500 m offices (B1) / education (D1), up to 5,000 m leisure (D2), up to 4,000 m restaurants & cafs and drinking establishments (A3 & A4), up to 3,000 m hotel (C1), up to 1,000 m hot food takeaways (A5), 500m health (D1), provision of up to 500 car parking spaces and a revised road alignment of (part of) Lewisham High Street, Rennell Street, Molesworth Street and Loampit Vale and works to Lewisham Road.
